- link: https://www.dw.com/en/world-in-progress-fukushima-10-years-on/av-56827627?maca=en-podcast_world-in-progress-1951-xml-mrss
  published: Wed, 10 Mar 2021 13:44:00 GMT
  summary: 'Fukushima in Japan, March 11, 2011. An earthquake, a tsunami and three
    nuclear meltdowns. Much has happened since then: Cities have been rebuilt, protective
    walls erected, work continued on the damaged nuclear power plant. Export restrictions
    for many products have been largely lifted. But only a few people who had to flee
    their homes ten years ago have actually returned to the region.'
  title: 'World in Progress: Fukushima 10 years on'
